1 2. Continuing education coursework may be provided by the national ground water
2 association, the North Dakota well drillers association, incorporated, a
3 board-sponsored workshop, the department of environmental quality, the state water
4 commission, or by any board-approved course provider.
5 3. A continuing education course must be preapproved by the board unless otherwise
6 provided under this section. A continuing education course provider or a certificate
7 holder shall request preapproval of continuing education coursework by submitting to
8 the board a course outline, the instructor's name, the length of the training, and an
9 explanation of how the training relates to the construction and service of water wells.
10 4. A certificate holder may request approval of education that was not preapproved by
11 submitting to the board verification of attendance, a course outline, and an explanation
12 of why preapproval was not obtained. The board shall determine on a case-by-case
13 basis whether to approve education that was not preapproved.
14 SECTION 3. REPEAL. Sections 43-35-11.1, 43-35-12, 43-35-13, 43-35-14, 43-35-16, and
15 43-35-17 of the North Dakota Century Code are repealed.
